records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by the State, Defense counsel and defendant.
Court sentenced defendant to serve 75  DAYS in the House of Correction consecutive to any sentence; credit for 4 days served. 

Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for one (1) year with the following conditions:
- Pay costs, fees, assessments and surcharges (including the DNA surcharge) during the term of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
- Provide a DNA sample, if not already done so
.  
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
